  "prompt": "What is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Treutlen County GA?",
  "response": "Finding the right inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center is a crucial step toward recovery. Near Treutlen County, Georgia, there are several reputable facilities you might consider:\n\n### 1. **ELEMENTS Behavioral Health**\n- **Location:** Macon, GA\n- **Services Offered:** Comprehensive inpatient treatment programs for substance use disorders, including detoxification, individual and group therapy, evidence-based practices, and aftercare planning.\n- **Website:** [ELEMENTS Behavioral Health](https://www.elementsbehavioral.com/)\n- **Contact Information:** \n  - Phone: (478) 655-5433\n  - Address: 601 Paseo Blvd, Macon, GA 31216\n\n### 2. **River Valley Recovery Center**\n- **Location:** Richmond Hill, GA\n- **Services Offered:** Inpatient and outpatient programs, personalized treatment plans, individual counseling, group therapy sessions, and family support services.\n- **Website:** [River Valley Recovery](https://www.rivervalleyrecovery.com/)\n- **Contact Information:** \n  - Phone: (770) 643-2178\n  - Address: 9155 Brandon Hwy, Richmond Hill, GA 31324\n\n### 3. **Better Days Recovery Centers**\n- **Location:** Macon, GA\n- **Services Offered:** Residential treatment, intensive outpatient programs, therapeutic services, relapse prevention, and wellness programs.\n- **Website:** [Better Days Recovery](https://www.betterdaysrecovery.com/)\n- **Contact Information:** \n  - Phone: (478) 853-6812\n  - Address: 3800 Ralph David Abernathy Blvd, Macon, GA 31206\n\n### 4. **Macon Treatment Centers**\n- **Location:** Macon, GA\n- **Services Offered:** Various inpatient and outpatient services tailored to individual needs, including medical detox, therapy, and support groups.\n- **Contact Information:** \n  - Phone: (478) 224-3650\n  - Address: 933 Coliseum Blvd Extension, Macon, GA 31217\n\n### Additional Resources:\n- **SAMHSA Treatment Locator:** The Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) offers an online treatment locator tool that can help you find accredited facilities based on your specific needs.\n  - **Website:** [SAMHSA Treatment Locator](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/)\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Rehab Center:\n1. **Assess the Services Offered:** Ensure the facility provides the specific treatments you or your loved one needs, such as detox, therapy, and aftercare support.\n2. **Check Accreditation:** Look for centers accredited by reputable organizations like the Joint Commission or CARF.\n3. **Consider Location:** Proximity to home can be important for family involvement, but some may prefer a location far enough to encourage focus on recovery.\n4. **Review Costs and Insurance:** Verify whether the center accepts your insurance or offers payment plans.\n5. **Visit the Facility:** If possible, visit the center to get a feel for the environment and ask questions about their programs and success rates.\n\n### Seeking Professional Guidance:\nIt's highly recommended to consult with a healthcare professional or a counselor specializing in addiction to help determine the best treatment option tailored to your specific situation.\n\nIf you're in immediate need of assistance, please reach out to a local healthcare provider or contact emergency services.",
